commit dcbd23f6208c99f85aa82d287d75a8eb5955000f
Author: Mathias Fussenegger <f.mathias@zignar.net>
Date:   Wed Sep 4 15:43:40 2024 +0200

    Fix race allowing to insert conflicting value/types into object(dynamic) columns
    
    Closes https://github.com/crate/crate/issues/16562
    
    The `ObjectIndexer` changed itself immediately when detecting new
    columns. This was a problem if concurrently another shard created the
    same column with a different type:
    
        shard 1: Detects obj['x'] as long, modifies itself
        shard 2: Detects obj['x'] as double, modifies itself
        shard 1: add column request a)
        shard 2: add column request b)
        add column request a) succeeds. cluster state updated to obj['x'] = long
        shard 1: receives success, continues
        shard 2: receives add column failure, skips 1 item due to the failure but continues with remaining items
        shard 2: remaining items are inserted as obj['x'] = double
    
    To fix this, this changed the `ObjectIndexer` to not immediately update
    its children on `collectSchemaUpdates`, but on `updateTargets`, which is
    only called after a add-column request succeeded

